attributes.name: doc-comment
arguments: @notice Attempts to fulfill a single order by matching it against multiple orders from a provided list.

attributes.name: doc-comment
arguments: @dev This function creates a new order with the given parameters and iterates through the list of existing orders,

attributes.name: doc-comment
arguments: attempting to match the new order with existing orders. It handles full and partial matches according to the specified limit type:

attributes.name: doc-comment
arguments: - 'GTC' (Good-Til-Canceled): The order remains active until it is either fully filled or canceled.

attributes.name: doc-comment
arguments: - 'IOC' (Immediate-Or-Cancel): The order can be partially filled immediately, and any unfilled portion is canceled.

attributes.name: doc-comment
arguments: - 'FOK' (Fill-Or-Kill): The order must be fully filled immediately, or the entire transaction fails.

attributes.name: doc-comment
arguments: @param amount The amount of the asset to be fulfilled in the new order.

attributes.name: doc-comment
arguments: @param order_type The type of the order being fulfilled (e.g., buy or sell).

attributes.name: doc-comment
arguments: @param limit_type The limit type for the new order: 'GTC', 'IOC', or 'FOK'.

attributes.name: doc-comment
arguments: @param price The price at which the new order is to be fulfilled.

attributes.name: doc-comment
arguments: @param slippage The maximum allowable slippage (as a percentage) for the price during the matching process.

attributes.name: doc-comment
arguments: @param orders A vector of order IDs representing the existing orders to match against the new order.

attributes.name: doc-comment
arguments: @return b256 The unique identifier of the newly created order. If the order is partially matched and canceled (in the case of 'IOC'), the ID corresponds to the canceled order.

arguments: read
